article.headline: Cleveland St. 66, Fla. International 58
article.story: MIAMI -- J'Nathan Bullock scored 16 points to lead Cleveland State to a 66-58 win against Florida International on Wednesday night. Bullock also chipped in seven rebounds and two blocks for the Vikings (4-2), who shot 46.2 percent (24 of 52) from the field en route to victory. Cedric Jackson and D'Aundray Brown scored 15 apiece, and Chris Moore added three blocks for Cleveland State. Tremayne Russell added a game-high 18 points for the Golden Panthers (3-3), who shot 39.1 percent (18 of 46) from the field in the loss. The Golden Panthers, who trailed by three points at halftime, led 46-43 with 9:13 remaining but the Vikings went on an 8-0 run from there and wouldn't lose the lead again.
